output.crosstab_text:
For First degree graduates of all subjects, 5 years after graduation, the industry with the highest proportion of female graduates is WHOLESALE AND RETAIL TRADE - REPAIR OF MOTOR VEHICLES AND MOTORCYCLES, and the median earnings of females in this industry were £26,300. The industry with the highest proportion of male graduates was ELECTRICITY, GAS, STEAM AND AIR CONDITIONING SUPPLY and the median earnings of males in this industry were £24,800

The biggest difference in proportions is seen in ARTS, ENTERTAINMENT AND RECREATION where the proportion of female graduates is 6.2 percentage points higher than the proportion of male graduates.

The biggest difference in median earnings is seen in FINANCIAL AND INSURANCE ACTIVITIES where the median earnings of male graduates were £2,200 higher than the medain earnings of female graduates.

The group with the highest earnings was female graduates in the OTHER SERVICE ACTIVITIESindustry (median earnings of £26,700).

10% of female graduates are concentrated in the top 2 industries (either MANUFACTURING or HUMAN HEALTH AND SOCIAL WORK ACTIVITIES), whereas for male graduates this is 3.8%.
